   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="diagnosis">
      <p>
Diagnosis
</p>
      <p>
Elytra with apical tubercles on interstriae III–VII (
Fig. 5A
), first stria almost twice as wide as than second stria, striae III–VII subequal in width and conspicuous (
Figs 1A
, 
4A
) and sub-medial area of endophallus with elongate scales (
Fig. 8A
, arrow) distinguish this species (for a complete description see 
González-Alvarado &amp; Vaz-de-Mello 2021
).
</p>
